\begin_layout Title
Something about s-wave scattering and long imaging times
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Me and Others
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Everyone loves the potential for p-wave superfluids.
 Raman coupling allows for that possiblity.
 But how do we know if they are truly p-wave? We'll have to actually scatter
 them and observe anisotropic distribution.
 First, develop methodology by s-wave scattering Fermi clouds at differnet
 feilds around the Feshbach resonance and observed the distribution.
 We developed a method to correct for recoil induced detuning during long
 imaging times using a simulation, and use it to process our s-wave scattering
 data.
 
\end_layout

